<item>
            <title>[VYSPER-265] XMLTokenizer does not keep state across parsed IoBuffers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VYSPER-265</link>
                <project id="12310930" key="VYSPER">VYSPER</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When receiving a large Stanza, some of the XML tokens&lt;br/&gt;
are not parsed properly. Specifically, tag names gets broken (i.e. instead of &quot;&amp;lt;item ...&amp;gt;&quot; i see &quot;&amp;lt;tem ...&amp;gt;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The XMLTokenizer does not keep state across two different IoBuffers that the XMLParser is parsing during stanza decoding.&lt;br/&gt;
It currently only keeps the last position in the tokenized IoBuffer, but when a new IoBuffer is tokenized, &lt;br/&gt;
the previous partial token content is lost.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Using Vysper for creating XMPP client based on Java NIO.</environment>
